## ğŸ§  Key Concepts
- ArrayList is a **resizable (dynamic) array**
- It is part of the **Java Collections Framework**
- Allows duplicate elements
- Maintains insertion order
- Provides built-in methods for easy operations

---

## âš™ï¸ Common Methods Used
- `add()`
- `get()`
- `set()`
- `remove()`
- `size()`
- `contains()`

---

## ğŸ§  Notes & Learnings
- Unlike arrays, ArrayList size can grow or shrink dynamically
- Indexing starts from **0**
- Internally uses an array to store elements
- Better suited when frequent insertions/removals are required

---

## ğŸ“Œ Best Practices
- Use generics (`ArrayList<Integer>`) to ensure type safety
- Prefer ArrayList over arrays when size is unknown
- Avoid unnecessary conversions between array and ArrayList

